parsing cover files and combining into a final file.
issue.body:
Ran into a wall while trying to parse the cover files. I was initially wanting to just modify the files itself. This would not be good if there are multiple files in your project and it creates a .cover file for each file in your project that ran through the test. So I was thinking of creating an output file which runs through the cover files. It'll have a different file type like .subtest. after running through each test case I would compile the subtests into a single file which contains all of the +/-. 

If you guys have any other ideas I'm open for suggestions.

issue.title: obtaining trace output from sys.stdout to a file
issue.body:
When I run the following lines. 

tracer = trace.Trace(count=False, trace=True)
tracer.runfunc(def, *args) 

I get a print out on the command line like: 

 --- modulename: Testrecurse, funcname: recurse
Testrecurse.py(2):     print 'recurse(%s)' % level
recurse(2)
Testrecurse.py(3):     if level:
Testrecurse.py(4):         recurse(level-1)
 --- modulename: Testrecurse, funcname: recurse
Testrecurse.py(2):     print 'recurse(%s)' % level
recurse(1)
Testrecurse.py(3):     if level:
Testrecurse.py(4):         recurse(level-1)
 --- modulename: Testrecurse, funcname: recurse
Testrecurse.py(2):     print 'recurse(%s)' % level
recurse(0)
Testrecurse.py(3):     if level:
Testrecurse.py(5):     return
Testrecurse.py(5):     return
Testrecurse.py(5):     return

Option 1: 
Change sys.stdout = outfile
Then when I'm done change it back with sys.stdout = sys.__stdout__

milestone.description:
Assumptions have been made in the system testing of existing github projects. the reason being that we have the following requirements for finding the suspiciousness values:
1. tests are in /test folder and start with prefix test_
2. source files are in /src folder
3. test cases return values 0 or 1 based on success or failure respectively

Assumptions have been made in the system testing of existing github projects. the reason being that we have the following requirements for finding the suspiciousness values:
1. tests are in /test folder and start with prefix test_
2. source files are in /src folder
3. test cases return values 0 or 1 based on success or failure respectively
